commText: Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Khaleel Ahmed will open the attack
Right, we're back for the chase. Rasikh Salam comes in for Shaw as an impact sub for DC

Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, FOUR, gorgeous shot to get started! Touch full and slanting away outside off, Saha pressed forward and into the drive, timed it so sweetly and it raced away to the deep cover fence
Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, no run, full and on the stumps, clipped straight to mid-wicket
Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, wide, pushed full and wide outside off, Saha reaches out looking to slice it away but it keeps going away from him
Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, 1 run, low full-toss outside off, Saha misses out as he finds cover with the drive

Khaleel Ahmed to Shubman Gill, 1 run, edged but it flies away! Full and slanting across outside off, Shubman Gill pushed at it, got a thick outside edge and it flew to the left of the man at backward point, wasn't all that far but just far enough
Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, 1 run, full and outside off, Saha throws his hands at it, slices it off a thick outside edge and it goes out towards deep backward point, man at third man gets around
Khaleel Ahmed to Shubman Gill, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, knocked towards mid-off for a quick single
Anrich Nortje, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Nortje to Shubman Gill, FOUR, beautifully played! Pitched up full and on the pads, Shubman Gill just used the pace and flicked it away gently through mid-wicket, all timing and placement
Nortje to Shubman Gill, no run, good length delivery nips into off-stump, Gill hangs back to defend and gets a thick inside edge onto the pads
Nortje to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Nortje to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Axar !! The skipper goes early! Full and on off-stump, seering pace and Gill looked to loft this over mid-off, no real footwork and it hit him high on the bat. Easy catch for Axar at mid-off. Big wicket for DC early doors. Shubman Gill c Axar b Nortje 6(5) [4s-1]
Sai Sudharsan, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, SIX, just over the man! Back of a length delivery wide outside off, Sai Sudharsan got under it and sliced it, just went over Kuldeep at third man! A taller man would've gobbled it up
Now Nortje goes round the wicket
Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, just back of a length on off-stump again, Sudharsan bunts it towards mid-on, no timing on that
Nortje to Saha, FOUR, races away because of the pace! Good length on middle-leg, Saha shuffled inside the line and just tucked it off his hips, went fine and to the fine-leg ropes
Khaleel Ahmed to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, tucked away towards wide mid-on for one

Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, FOUR, no shortage of boundaries here! Length delivery on middle, bit of a half-tracker and Saha swiped it away through to the square leg ropes, not the best of timing but he put it far enough away from the man at fine-leg

Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, FOUR, just enough to get it over! Fuller on middle, Saha looked to loft it over mid-on and it went off the inner half, bat turned in his hand but he got just enough to take it over mid-wicket, outfield did the rest
Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, no run, full and wide outside off, driven straight to extra cover

Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, 2 runs, full and on the stumps, another swipe from Saha and no real timing, takes the inside half of the bat again and races past mid-wicket, this time the man at deep square leg gets around to keep it down to a couple

Khaleel Ahmed to Saha, SIX, no timing but more runs! It's not pretty but it's working for Saha at the moment, length delivery outside off, was pace off too, Saha looked to loft it over long-on, was probably through the shot a touch early but he went through with it, bottom hand came off and it went high, got enough to just about clear the ropes too
Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, no run, good length delivery outside off, angles in from round the wicket and rushes him as he looks to cut it

Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, length delivery wide outside off, full pace and Sai Sudharsan reached out and upper-cut it, got it very fine and to the right of the man at third man, wasn't far from, the fielder again
Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, smashed through the covers! Length delivery outside off, bit of width again and Sai Sudharsan slapped it through the gap at cover
Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, no run, length delivery on off-stump, punched straight to cover
Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, no run, banged in short on middle, Sai Sudharsan gets under it, that was zippy, called one for the over
Nortje to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 153.9kph, short of length on off-stump, rushes him with pace again as he mistimed a pull towards mid-wicket
Rasikh Dar Salam, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, no run, put down! Oh dear, that was a simple chance! Full on off-stump, Sai Sudharsan looked to loft that over mid-on through the line, got no timing and lobbed up straight to Axar at mid-on off the inner half, simplest of chances and Axar put it down after juggling it a few times! You don't see him put down too many
Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, beautiful shot! Good length delivery just outside off, Sai Sudharsan watched it closely and punched it right into the gap at extra cover
Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, no run, slower delivery full and outside off, Sai Sudharsan pushed at it and was taken aback by the lack of pace
Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, tight run! Low full-toss on middle, Sai Sudharsan clipped it towards mid-wicket and ran through for a sharp single, direct-hit and he was gone at the other end

Rasikh Salam to Saha, FOUR, he doesn't need to time them to get runs! Full on off-stump, Saha lofted it over mid-off, no timing again and off the inside half of the bat, just got it over the man at mid-off
Rasikh Salam to Saha, 1 run, slower delivery full on off-stump, mistimed slog again, takes a thick inside edge and goes towards square leg
Mukesh Kumar, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Saha, no run, length delivery on middle, Saha shuffled across looking to pull it fine and was struck on the thigh pad
Mukesh Kumar to Saha, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, dragged towards mid-on for one, no timing once more

Mukesh Kumar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, now a misfield! Things are going GT's way at the moment! Length delivery outside off, Sai Sudharsan crunched the cut shot, went straight to Nortje who ran a few paces to his left, just got an odd bounce and it jumped off his hand and into the ropes
Mukesh Kumar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, length delivery outside off, cut away hard to deep point again, this time Nortje makes no mistake
Mukesh Kumar to Saha, 1 run, full on off-stump, driven towards mid-on for a quick single
Mukesh Kumar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, length delivery on off-stump, punched straight to extra cover
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Over Summary (1-6 ov) * Both Saha and Gill get going with a boundary each * Gill holes out to Axar Patel off Nortje for 6 * A first-ball six for Sai Sudharsan as Nortje concedes 15 in his 1st over * Khaleel concedes 17 runs in the third over * Sai Sudharsan dropped by Axar off Rasikh Dar on 17
Axar to Saha, 1 run, length delivery outside off, bunted out towards sweeper cover for one
Highest powerplay scores for GT 78/0 vs LSG, Ahmedabad, 2023 67/1 vs DC, Delhi, 2024 65/1 vs SRH, Ahmedabad, 2023 65/1 vs CSK, Ahmedabad, 2023 64/1 vs RR, Kolkata, 2022
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, flatter delivery just outside off, punched out to sweeper cover
Axar to Saha, no run, length delivery just outside off, Saha backs away a long way to make room and mistimes it back to the bowler
DC review. They went to have another look at a lbw shout that was turned down, might have been going down leg

Axar to Saha, no run, review lost, full and drifting on to the pads, Saha had shuffled across just a little and was beaten on the inside edge as he looked to turn it into the leg-side, UltraEdge shows no bat and Hawkeye shows it would've gone well down leg, that didn't turn nearly enough to come back and hit the stumps
Axar to Saha, no run, flatter delivery just outside off, Saha punches it straight to backward point
Axar to Saha, 2 runs, length delivery on middle, Saha presses back and works it gently towards square leg for a couple
Kuldeep Yadav, comes into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, no run, loopy delivery onto leg stump, clipped towards mid-wicket. Saha wanted a single but was sent back
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, on a length outside off, pushed quicker and skids on after pitching. Sai Sudharsan connects late on the cut to get it to the right of short third for a boundary
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, pushed through and goes on with the arm towards leg. Tucked to deep square off the backfoot
Kuldeep Yadav to Saha, no run, pushed quicker and fuller at the stumps. Saha nearly chips it back to Kuldeep, to the right of him
Kuldeep Yadav to Saha, wide, too far wide outside off
Kuldeep Yadav to Saha, 1 run, flat delivery onto off stump, cut square of the wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, flat length ball at the stumps. The batter stays deep and slaps it to the left of long-on

Time-out. Gujarat have started well with the chase but the last couple of overs have been difficult with the spinners operating from both ends. GT have been a good chasing side and Delhi's death bowling this season has been a real concern. This game could have a very interesting end here...
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, angling onto the pads, tucked to mid-wicket
Axar to Saha, 1 run, quicker and with the arm towards middle. A quiet push to the left of covers for a single
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, flat delivery outside off, gets a bit of extra bounce. Sai Sudharshan stays back to ride the bounce nicely and cuts it powerfully in front of square for a boundary
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, superb timing!! Full on the pads, Sai Sudharsan plays a neat glance that goes between deep mid-wicket and long-on for a boundary
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, quicker and on the pads, clipped softly towards deep square for a couple of runs
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, arm ball outside off, on a length. Cut square of the wicket for a single
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short and spinning away outside off. An uppish cut shot towards sweeper cover for a single
Kuldeep Yadav to Saha, 1 run, short of length, a bit of a half tracker. Saha rocked back for a big slog but gets it off the bottom end to the right of Kuldeep for a single
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, on the pads, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Saha, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Saha, out Caught by Axar!! Gone!! A flat delivery that spins away outside off. Was too wide and Saha went for a big slash at it. Felt like he got enough bat to get it over the infield, but Axar jumps up nearly 9 feet to pluck it out of thin air. A wicket out of nowhere for the home side. 100th IPL catch for Axar. Saha c Axar b Kuldeep Yadav 39(25) [4s-5 6s-1]
Azmatullah Omarzai, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Yadav to Azmatullah, 1 run, darted through on a length, cut to sweeper cover

Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, on a length and spinning back in. Sai Sudharsan stays back and tucks it to the left of long-on for a couple of runs. That's a fifty for the southpaw, the first fifty by a guy not called Shubman Gill for GT this season.
Axar to Azmatullah, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Axar to Azmatullah, out Caught by Fraser-McGurk!! Another bit of magic in the field! An arm ball into the body, in the swinging arc and Omarzai went for a big slog through the line. Doesn't time it off the middle and Fraser-McGurk from deep mid-wicket rushes in and dives forward on a ball that was dying down on him. We've seen so many such catches go down in the IPL this season, but the young Aussie makes absolutely no mistake. Azmatullah c Fraser-McGurk b Axar 1(2)
David Miller, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Axar to Miller, 1 run, length ball on off stump, pushed down to long-on
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, pushed fuller and quicker, Sai Sudharsan with a slight shimmy turns it towards long-on
Axar to Miller, 1 run, on a length on off, Miller stays in his crease and punches it to the right of covers
Axar to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, flat and on the pads, swept powerfully towards deep backward square leg but Mukesh Kumar with an extended right hand saves the boundary

Axar to Sai Sudharsan, SIX, pushed much quicker and with the arm towards off stump. Sai Sudharsan plays a slog sweep across the line and down the ground. Had his heart in his mouth for a moment as Stubbs flew to his right from long-on and nearly plucked out another blinder. However, the bll wins this time around
Kuldeep Yadav to Miller, FOUR, tossed up a bit onto off, Miller shuffles in and sweeps it behind square. Got a bit of a top edge on it but lands safely to the right of the fielder for a boundary
Kuldeep Yadav to Miller, 1 run, pushed quicker onto leg stump, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, no run, on a length and stays straight outside off. Goes under Sai Sudharsan's bat and to the keeper who can't gather it
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, on the pads, turned softly towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, on a length and spinning in onto the pads, turned to deep backward square leg
Kuldeep Yadav to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, flighted up outside off, driven down to long-off.
Back to some pace bowling. Rasikh Salam into the attack. Pant keeping up to him
Rasikh Dar Salam [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, no run, very full outside off, driven to extra cover
Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, fuller off cutter on off stump, clipped towards deep square
Rasikh Salam to Miller, 1 run, length ball angling towards off, punched to extra cover for a single
Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Axar!! Holes out!! Axar is like a magnet that the ball is following today on the field. A fuller length delivery that was nice and tight at the stumps. Sai Sudharsan shimmies out and tries to chip it down the ground. Didn't get fully under it and goes straight down the throat of long-off. Rasikh Salam is pumped with that breakthrough! Sai Sudharsan c Axar b Rasikh Salam 65(39) [4s-7 6s-2]
Shahrukh Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Rasikh Salam to Shahrukh Khan, no run, on a length and angles in sharply after pitching. Beaten on the inside edge and just over the stumps. Thuds onto Pant on the thighs and he's in a bit of pain. Deflects towards short fine

Rasikh Salam to Shahrukh Khan, SIX, Rasikh shortens the length slightly with Pant standing back now. Shahrukh Khan was waiting for something like that. Stays deep and pulls this dibbly dobbly paced delivery over deep mid-wicket into the stands for a maximum!

Over Summary (7-13 ov) * Saha survives a LBW review by the Capitals on 34 * Axar Patel concedes 13 runs in the 9th over * Kuldeep strikes, Saha gets caught by Axar for 39 * Sai Sudharsan brings up a fine 29-ball half-century * Axar strikes next; Omarzai holes out to deep mid-wicket for 1 * Sai Sudharsan dismissed by Rasikh Dar, for a 39-ball 65
Mukesh Kumar [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Miller, 1 run, hard length delivery that was angling across. Pulled along the ground to deep mid-wicket.
Pant up to the stumps again
Mukesh Kumar to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, length ball on off, hit back towards Mukesh who parries it towards long-off
Mukesh Kumar to Miller, 1 run, length ball at the stumps, pulled towards deep mid-wicket
Not too much dew on the outfield, good sign for DC
Mukesh Kumar to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, right in the blockhole from Mukesh Kumar. Dug out to the left of the bowler for a single. Very well directed yorker
Mukesh Kumar to Miller, FOUR, short of length and offering a bit too much width. Miller punches it away powerfully in front of square for a boundary. A much needed boundary

Mukesh Kumar to Miller, FOUR, overpitched and outside off, Miller drills it into the ground and that initial momentum gets it over extra cover for another boundary. The final two balls ruin what was looking like a quiet over
Equation: 86 needed off 36 balls. Remember, DC scored 97 off just the last five
Rasikh Salam to Shahrukh Khan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rasikh Salam to Shahrukh Khan, out Caught by Pant!! Sharp take from the skipper!! We saw a glimpse of Rishabh Pant the batter in the first innings, and now a solid effort behind the stumps from RP. A length ball just outside off from Rasikh Salam. Shahrukh went for a big slog across the line and gets a faint edge on it. Pant got right behind in and covered the ball with both gloves to end the stay of Shahrukh Khan prematurely. Shahrukh Khan c Pant b Rasikh Salam 8(5) [6s-1]
Rahul Tewatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rasikh Salam to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, length ball on the pads, tucked towards deep backward square leg
Rasikh Salam to Miller, FOUR, fuller and just outside off, Miller plays it late and tactfully opens the bat face to get it between backward point and short third for a boundary. I0$
Rasikh Salam to Miller, 1 run, on a length and angling onto off, Miller dabs it towards short third for a single
Rasikh Salam to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, length ball on leg stump, clipped towards deep backward square leg
Rasikh Salam to Miller, 1 run, pace off and full, Miller runs it down towards backward point for a single
The big final over of Kuldeep coming up...
Kuldeep Yadav [3.0-0-24-1] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Miller, 1 run, loopy delivery outside off, drilled to the right of long-off. Just a single
Kuldeep Yadav to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, flat delivery angling onto the pads, turned to deep backward square leg

Kuldeep Yadav to Miller, 1 run, shuffles in to get in line with this flat delivery on off stump. Pulled powerfully to the right of deep mid-wicket. Felt like a boundary with the contact Miller made off it, but Fraser-McGurk was so quick to move across and save three runs
Kuldeep Yadav to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, dances out and Kuldeep slows it down and shortens the length. Pushed to the right of the bowler for a single
Kuldeep Yadav to Miller, 1 run, fired in from a fuller length, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Rahul Tewatia, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Rahul Tewatia, out Caught by Pant!! Gonski! A flat delivery that spun away after pitching. Was a bit too wide outside off and Tewatia went chasing for a big slash. Gets a faint tickle on that one and once again Pant has his gloves right behind it. Kuldeep strikes off his last ball. Rahul Tewatia c Pant b Kuldeep Yadav 4(5)
Most dismissals as a wicketkeeper in the IPL 185 - MS Dhoni 170 - Dinesh Karthik 112 - Wriddhiman Saha 92 - Rishabh Pant 90 - Robin Uthappa

Time-Out. Kuldeep has bowled a dream final over, conceding just five runs and getting the wicket of Tewatia. Delhi are in the driver's seat now but this IPL has shown no target is ever really safe. Miller will look to upset the hosts, but is the target too stiff?
Rashid Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Anrich Nortje [2.0-0-24-1] is back into the attack
Nortje to Miller, FOUR, 146.5 clicks, length ball at the stumps. Miller clears that front leg and slams it through a vacant mid-wicket region. One bounce and over

Nortje to Miller, SIX, 150.1 clicks, Nortje goes wider and a tad fuller. Miller reaches out and hits it through the line. Up and over extra cover and for a flat six. The pace of Anrich Nortje is no bother for a fellow countryman
Nortje to Miller, no run, pace off and short of length. Miller early on the pull and gets it off the bottom back onto the pitch

Nortje to Miller, SIX, what a hit!! They really need to check what these modern day bats are made off because this was just a gentle push down the ground that goes all the way. An attempted yorker that ends as a low full toss, Miller gets under it and chips it over the bowler for a sixer!!
Nortje to Miller, SIX, Anrich Nortje goes short on off stump. Not a bother for the man who's played so much cricket on bouncy tracks!! Pulled away nonchalantly over deep square leg for a maximum

Nortje to Miller, 2 runs, yorker length, nails the execution much better this time. Squeezed to the right of deep mid-wicket and well stopped by the fielder to save a couple of runs. A massive 24 runs off that over! 50 for David Miller
Mukesh Kumar [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, 1 run, dropped!! A length ball on off, slammed down towards deep square leg and was a fairly easy chance in the deep. Abhishek Porel is the fielder. First bit of ordinary fielding today where we've seen some brilliant catches

Mukesh Kumar to Miller, FOUR, 138.3 clicks, yorker length delivery targetting those boots. Miller clears the front leg to make space for his bat and glance through square leg for a boundary. He's playing a real blinder here!
Mukesh Kumar to Miller, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Miller, out Caught by Rasikh Salam!! A collective sigh of relief across the Arun Jaitley Stadium as Rasikh Salam gets both hands under the ball and holds on to the catch. Mukesh Kumar persists with the yorker length, Miller couldn't completely dig it out this time and doesn't time it off the middle. Holes out to deep square leg where a fielder was placed just the previous ball. Miller c Rasikh Salam b Mukesh Kumar 55(23) [4s-6 6s-3]
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Sai Kishore, 1 run, length ball on leg, tucked to dep mid-wicket
Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, no ball, too far outside off, so far wide that it ends outside the pitch. Will be a no ball and freehit!
Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, 1 run, solid execution with the wide yorker, drilled towards long-off. Just a single

Mukesh Kumar to Sai Kishore, leg byes, FOUR, fuller delivery onto leg stump, Sai Kishore shuffles inwards for a scoop and can't connect. Deflects off his pads to the right of the keeper for four leg byes. DC review for LBW but the ball pitched outside leg
Rasikh Dar Salam [3.0-0-26-2] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Rashid Khan, wide, pace off and wide, too wide outside off
Rasikh Salam to Rashid Khan, FOUR, tries a yorker and errs with an ankle high full toss on leg stump. Rashid helps it on its way towards the fine leg boundary

Rasikh Salam to Rashid Khan, 1 run, solid effort in the field!! Perhaps a match winning effort. A back of the hand slower delivery onto off, Rashid gets under it and slams it down the ground. Looked like it was heading for a flat six but Stubbs jumps in from nowhere, catches the ball and throws it back onto the field as he was falling over.
Rasikh Salam to Sai Kishore, no run, pace off and wide outside off. A big swing and a miss for Sai Kishore. Dot ball!

Rasikh Salam to Sai Kishore, SIX, out of here!! Shuffles in to gather this full delivery outside off and slams it across the line. Plenty of elevation but gets the required distance as well to get it over cow corner for six! Don't go anywhere, this match is still alive

Rasikh Salam to Sai Kishore, SIX, six more!! What is it about GT finding unlikely left handed heroes in crunch situations. A full delivery onto off, Sai Kishore shuffles in and swings it down the ground. The safest place to hit the ball for a flat six!!
Rasikh Salam to Sai Kishore, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Rasikh Salam to Sai Kishore, out Bowled!! Bowled em!! I0$! Trusts his yorker from round the wicket, angles it in at pace. Sai Kishore goes for a big swing across the line but misses, and Salam strikes timber. Sai Kishore b Rasikh Salam 13(6) [6s-2]
Equation: 19 off the last 6 balls. Stoinis got 17 yesterday with three to spare!
Mohit Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, FOUR, there comes the snake slot!! And it is stinging DC. Mukesh Kumar errs with the yorker, dishes out a slot ball and Rashid Khan shuffles in and swings it through cow corner for a boundary!!

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, FOUR, length ball outside off, was pace off. Rashid Khan gets closer and smokes it over extra cover. Powerfully hit and over the infield into a vacant part of the ground for four!!

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, no run, jeez!! A full toss just outside off. Rashid Khan went for a big slog and gets an inside edge on it. Onto the ground and towards Pant who parries it towards short third who readjusts very well. Mohit Sharma nearly ran twice as Rashid sent him back. Dot ball. A review from GT for a no ball but below the waist.

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, no run, low full toss, very difficult to get under those!! Slammed towards Axar Patel at deep mid-wicket. Once again Mohit Sharma runs till the batter and then is sent back.
All on Rashid. Two sixes needed!!

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, SIX, out of here!! A wide yorker, was a bit undercooked and Rashid Khan gets under it and smokes it towards the left of long-off for a maximum. Over the leaping fielder and into the crowds...
Still all three results possible...

Mukesh Kumar to Rashid Khan, no run, Mukesh Kumar holds his nerve!! Delhi escape a real scare... Yorker length delivery and Rashid Khan can't get under it. Slams it down the ground but not off the middle. Ambles towards Stubbs at long-on after a couple of bounces. GT don't even complete the single, Delhi win by 4 runs.

23:15 Local Time, 17:45 GMT, 23:15 IST: This IPL isn't doing any favours to heart patients or people with high blood pressure. So many oscillations in the result. One moment Delhi were dominating, then Gujarat looked like favourites but ultimately it was a target too stiff as DC squeeze through with two points. Chasing a stiff target, GT suffered a big blow as skipper Shubman Gill was out cheaply. Saha scored a sketchy 39, getting many mishits over the infield thanks to the powerplay, as Sai Sudharshan made his mark from the other end. The southpaw scored a neat looking fifty and was looking in control of things before Rasikh Salam nabbed him with a slower delivery. DC seemed to always get wickets when they wanted, and it felt like it was just about going through the motions. However, David Miller had other plans. He took down his countryman Nortje was a 24 run over and got to a fifty in no time. The southpaw however was dismissed by Mukesh Kumar. GT got two more cameos from Sai Kishore and Rashid Khan, but still fell short by 4 runs. I0$ Stick around for the presentations...

Shubman Gill | GT Captain - I think we played some really good cricket, disappointing to lose in the end, but great character shown by everyone. Great fight till the end and we never thought we were out of the game at any point. When you're chasing 224, there's no point in talking about plans, just go out and score runs. I think impact player has a bit of a role (in making the matches high scoring), even if you lose extra wickets, extra cushion is there for the batters to keep going and it gives the license for the batters to keep going till the end. At one stage, we thought we would be able to restrict them to 200-210, but we gave away some extra runs in the last 2-3 overs. But this is a smallish ground, we spoke about the same when we went out to chase. Execution becomes very important, if there's a set batter or a finisher, you'll have to execute well. It's okay if there's something in the wicket, but on pitches like this, you'll have to make sure that you execute all your plans perfectly, be it the yorkers or the variations.

Kuldeep Yadav: Happy to get the win. These two points are very important. Amazing game. When we went into the last over, knew it was going to be very tight. We had a plan, coach and captain wanted one over when Tewatia came into bat. Luckily it worked out. You have to read the batsmen and see what they are trying to do. We batted well, 225 is a good total. I didn’t want to try too much when I came into bowl. Just focused on my lines and lengths and saw what the batters were trying to do. (On Tewatia’s wicket) I bowled a few balls into the wicket to him, thought he might slog-sweep, it was a good plan from the keeper and we got the wicket.
